{"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OpenXRAction"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OpenXRAction","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"OpenXRAction","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot12OpenXRActionC"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OpenXRAction","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An OpenXR action."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Resource"],"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From"},{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"],"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OpenXRAction","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This resource defines an OpenXR action. Actions can be used both for inputs (buttons\/joystick\/trigger\/etc) and outputs (haptics)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OpenXR performs automatic conversion between action type and input type whenever possible. An analog trigger bound to a boolean action will thus return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" if the trigger is depressed and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if pressed fully."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Actions are not directly bound to specific devices, instead OpenXR recognizes a limited number of top level paths that identify devices by usage. We can restrict which devices an action can be bound to by these top level paths. For instance an action that should only be used for hand held controllers can have the top level paths “\/user\/hand\/left” and “\/user\/hand\/right” associated with them. See the [url=https:\/\/www.khronos.org\/registry\/OpenXR\/specs\/1.0\/html\/xrspec.html#semantic-path-reserved]reserved path section in the OpenXR specification[\/url] for more info on the top level paths."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the name of the resource is used to register the action with."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/openxraction"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OpenXRAction\/actionType-swift.property","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OpenXRAction\/localizedName","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OpenXRAction\/toplevelPaths"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OpenXRAction\/godotClassName"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OpenXRAction\/ActionType-swift.enum"],"title":"Enumerations"}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/VariantRepresentable":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"VariantRepresentable","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantRepresentable"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Types that conform to VariantRepresentable can be stored directly in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with no conversion.  These include all of the Variant types from Godot (for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example ","type":"text"},{"code":"GString","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Rect"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Plane","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), Godot objects (those that subclass","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftGodot.Object) as well as the built-in Swift types UInt8, Int64 and Double."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantRepresentable","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variantrepresentable"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","title":"SwiftGodot","role":"collection","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/OpenXRAction/toplevelPaths":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A collections of toplevel paths to which this action can be bound.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/openxraction\/toplevelpaths","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toplevelPaths"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PackedStringArray","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot17PackedStringArrayC","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"title":"toplevelPaths","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OpenXRAction\/toplevelPaths","role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/s23CustomStringConvertibleP":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","type":"unresolvable","title":"Swift.CustomStri